summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of North Sixty-seventh Street, in the City of Seattle, from Woodlawn Avenue to East Green Lake Boulevard, by grading and curbing the same, and constructing concrete sidewalks thereon, in accordance with Resolution No. 1788 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
